 lettres du Qu&eacute;bec (2001-2002); Rector&#8217;s Cabinet Special Funding, Concordia University (2002), Renata Hornstein Graduate Fellowship in Recognition of Superior Academic Achievement (2003); Concordia University Retired Faculty and Staff Graduate Award in Recognition of Superior Academic Achievement (2003); and another Recherche et cr&eacute;ation: Bourse B from Conseil des arts et des lettres du Qu&eacute;bec (2005-2006), amongst others. </p></div><?php include('_includes/footer.inc'); ?>